### ============================================
### Travaily Auth API - Testing File
### Use with VS Code "REST Client" extension
### Run each request in order (top to bottom)
### ============================================

@baseUrl = http://localhost:3000


### ─── 1. SIGNUP ─────────────────────────────────
### Creates a new user + generates OTP (check terminal for OTP)
POST {{baseUrl}}/auth/signup
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "name": "John Doe",
  "email": "john@example.com",
  "password": "secret123"
}

### ─── 2. SIGNUP (Duplicate - Should return 400) ──
POST {{baseUrl}}/auth/signup
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "name": "John Doe",
  "email": "john@example.com",
  "password": "secret123"
}

### ─── 3. SIGNUP (Validation Error - Should return 400) ──
POST {{baseUrl}}/auth/signup
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "name": "",
  "email": "not-an-email",
  "password": "123"
}

### ─── 4. LOGIN ──────────────────────────────────
### Returns JWT token - copy it for protected routes later
POST {{baseUrl}}/auth/login
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "email": "john@example.com",
  "password": "secret123"
}

### ─── 5. LOGIN (Wrong Password - Should return 401) ──
POST {{baseUrl}}/auth/login
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "email": "john@example.com",
  "password": "wrongpassword"
}

### ─── 6. LOGIN (Non-existent User - Should return 401) ──
POST {{baseUrl}}/auth/login
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "email": "nobody@example.com",
  "password": "secret123"
}

### ─── 7. SEND OTP ───────────────────────────────
### Check your terminal console for the OTP code
POST {{baseUrl}}/auth/send-otp
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "email": "john@example.com"
}

### ─── 8. VERIFY OTP ─────────────────────────────
### Replace "123456" with the OTP from your terminal
POST {{baseUrl}}/auth/verify-otp
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "email": "john@example.com",
  "code": "123456"
}

### ─── 9. VERIFY OTP (Invalid Code - Should return 400) ──
POST {{baseUrl}}/auth/verify-otp
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "email": "john@example.com",
  "code": "000000"
}

### ─── 10. FORGOT PASSWORD ───────────────────────
### Check your terminal console for the reset OTP
POST {{baseUrl}}/auth/forgot-password
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "email": "john@example.com"
}

### ─── 11. RESET PASSWORD ────────────────────────
### Replace "123456" with the OTP from your terminal
POST {{baseUrl}}/auth/reset-password
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "email": "john@example.com",
  "code": "123456",
  "newPassword": "newSecret456"
}

### ─── 12. LOGIN WITH NEW PASSWORD ───────────────
### Verify the password was actually changed
POST {{baseUrl}}/auth/login
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "email": "john@example.com",
  "password": "newSecret456"
}
